HEADWORD: Crithomancy
<hw>Crith"o*man`cy</hw> <pr>(kr⟦icr⟧th"⟦osl⟧*m⟦acr⟧n`s⟦ycr⟧)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <grk>kriqai`</grk>, pl., barley +
<ets>-mancy</ets>: cf. F. <ets>crithomancie</ets>.]</ety> <def>A kind of
divination by means of the dough of the cakes offered in the ancient
sacrifices, and the meal strewed over the victims.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

